TIP: How to test if your dye is ready to be removed/wiped off.

A quick tip for you on how I create a deep even staining with dye. 

Once I’ve allowed the dye to develop i grab a dry cotton tip and press it along the brow to see if any dye transfers. If there is no transfer, then it’s ready to be removed. 

Doing this step will ensure you have a nice even deep staining.

Browcode Stain Application is a little different to other dye applications. It stains very quickly so you have to apply the dye very quickly and precisely. Always starts at the tail first and make your way to the front. You can apply it in a thick even layer on the tails and then gradually make the layer thinner as you come to the fronts.

Brow Lamination Aftercare! Now that you’re flaunting those perfectly styled arches, let’s make sure they stay flawless. 

Here’s your Brow Lamination Aftercare 101:

🌿 Keep them Dry: Avoid water and steam for the next 24 hours. Your brows are still stabilising and need time to set.

🧴 Gentle Care: Apply a nourishing brow oil daily to keep your brows hydrated and looking their best.

🚫 Hands Off: Resist the urge to touch, rub, or play with your freshly laminated brows – we want them to stay sleek!

🕶 Skip the Sauna: Steer clear of saunas, hot tubs, and intense workouts for the first couple of days to prevent them from over processing from the heat. 

Remember, your brows are your new BFFs – treat them kindly, and they’ll always be on point! 

Have any questions? Drop them in the comments below or DM us. 

#BrowLamination #AftercareEssentials”

How I create an Ombré Effect with Browcode Stain.

1. First off, apply the dye starting at the tail first and work your way towards the front. 
2. When you get to the front apply a thinner layer. 
3. Before going onto the next brows. Use a microswab that is slightly damp with water and start brushing the dye upwards passed the mapping lines. The water will dilute the dye making it a lighter and softer colour. 
4. Once you’ve finished doing the above steps on both brows, go back to the first brow you did and remove about 1-1.5cm off the fronts. 
5. After the dye has dried (5-10 mins usually in my salon) remove the middle of the brow with a cotton tip dipped in water. 
6. After another 5 minutes remove the rest of the dye with a damp cotton round. 

Please note: Timings will vary depending on shades you choose, how deep of a stain you want, the clients skin type, how long it takes to dry and your application.
